<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-11-01</DATELINE><TITLE>The Tracheal Microbiota in Patients with a Tracheostomy Before, During, and After an Acute Respiratory Infection</TITLE><BODY>Examining tracheal microbiota before, during, and after acute respiratory infection (ARI) in patients with a tracheostomy demonstrated large baseline intra-patient microbiota variability and a significant bloom of Haemophilus and Moraxella on day 1 of ARI symptoms. The tracheal microbiota community composition changed significantly from baseline to 1 month after ARI.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>